nevitable, and hence that a form of paternalism cannot be avoided. He urges that there are profoundly moral reasons to ensure that choice architecture is helpful rather than harmful-and that it makes people’s lives better and longer.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChoice (Psychology)xEconomic aspectsxUnited States. 0aChoice (Psychology)xEconomic aspectszUnited States. 0aConsumer behaviorxPolitical aspectsxUnited States. 0aConsumer behaviorxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aLibertarianismxUnited States. 0aLibertarianismzUnited States. 0aPaternalismxPolitical aspectsxUnited States. 0aPaternalismxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Freedom.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030020692040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300206920423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300206920/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles